>> command to list the files in current directory
ls
>> we can use "touch" command to create an empty file, example "touch file_name"
>> command to search for a word
grep word file_name
Example:
grep fetching * --> this will search for the word fetching in all the files in current directory
grep fetching log_04072025 --> this will search for the word fetching in log_04072025 file

>> how can i display the content of a file
cat file_name

>> how can I edit the file
use vim editor
step-1: vim file_name
step-2: type the letter "i" in your keyboard to enter in to write mode
step-3: start writing the content in to the file
step-4: type "esc" then type ":wq"
